WEBVTT

00:02.769 --> 00:04.704
- ♪ TIMMY IS AN AVERAGE KID ♪

00:04.771 --> 00:07.507
♪ THAT NO ONE UNDERSTANDS ♪

00:07.574 --> 00:11.378
♪ MOM AND DAD AND VICKY
ALWAYS GIVING HIM COMMANDS ♪

00:11.444 --> 00:12.879
- BED, TWERP!

00:12.946 --> 00:14.948
- ♪ THE DOOM AND GLOOM
UP IN HIS ROOM ♪

00:15.014 --> 00:17.283
♪ IS BROKEN INSTANTLY ♪

00:17.350 --> 00:19.886
♪ BY HIS MAGIC LITTLE FISH
WHO GRANT HIS EVERY WISH ♪

00:19.953 --> 00:21.321
♪ 'CAUSE IN REALITY ♪

00:21.388 --> 00:23.390
♪ THEY ARE HIS ODDPARENTS ♪

00:23.456 --> 00:24.691
♪ FAIRLY ODDPARENTS ♪

00:24.758 --> 00:25.792
- WANDS AND WINGS.

00:25.859 --> 00:27.260
- FLOAT-Y CROWN-Y THINGS.

00:27.327 --> 00:29.696
- ♪ ODDPARENTS,
FAIRLY ODDPARENTS ♪

00:29.763 --> 00:32.098
♪ REALLY MOD, PEA POD,
BUFF BOD, HOT ROD ♪

00:32.165 --> 00:34.667
- OBTUSE, RUBBER GOOSE,
GREEN MOOSE, GUAVA JUICE,

00:34.734 --> 00:38.538
GIANT SNAKE, BIRTHDAY CAKE,
LARGE FRIES, CHOCOLATE SHAKE!

00:38.605 --> 00:40.840
- ♪ ODDPARENTS,
FAIRLY ODDPARENTS ♪

00:40.907 --> 00:42.842
{\an8}♪ IT FLIPS YOUR LID
WHEN YOU ARE THE KID ♪

00:42.909 --> 00:44.611
{\an8}♪ WITH FAIRLY ODDPARENTS ♪

00:44.677 --> 00:45.712
{\an8}- YEAH, RIGHT.

01:01.928 --> 01:02.962
- HI, TIMMY.

01:03.029 --> 01:04.763
- [screams]
DON'T EAT ME!

01:04.831 --> 01:06.366
- I WOULD NEVER EAT YOU,
TIMMY.

01:06.433 --> 01:09.169
BESIDES, I JUST ATE THE DOG FOOD
YOUR MOM MADE FOR DINNER.

01:09.235 --> 01:10.537
- THAT WAS MEAT LOAF.

01:10.603 --> 01:12.705
- OH, THEN I TOOK
A BULLET FOR YOU THERE.

01:12.772 --> 01:14.441
- [screams]

01:14.507 --> 01:17.076
- SPORT, YOU'VE BEEN
SCREAMING ALL MORNING.

01:17.143 --> 01:18.711
WHY ARE YOU SO JUMPY?

01:18.778 --> 01:21.181
- BECAUSE I'M GOING
ON A CAMPING TRIP

01:21.247 --> 01:24.083
WITH MY SQUIRRELY SCOUT TROOP,
AND MY DAD IS THE TROOP LEADER.

01:24.150 --> 01:26.152
[all scream]

01:26.219 --> 01:27.654
- WHAT'S WRONG
WITH YOUR DAD?

01:27.720 --> 01:29.222
- EVERY TIME WE GO
ON A CAMPING TRIP,

01:29.289 --> 01:31.791
MY DAD PUTS US
IN TERRIBLE DANGER.

01:31.858 --> 01:33.760
- WATCH AND LEARN, SCOUTS.

01:33.827 --> 01:35.728
BEEHIVES ARE NATURE'S PINATA.

01:35.795 --> 01:37.096
[bees buzz]

01:37.163 --> 01:39.766
[all scream]

01:39.833 --> 01:42.936
TO START A FIRE,
JUST RUB TWO STICKS TOGETHER.

01:43.002 --> 01:44.571
- THAT'S DYNAMITE, DAD!

01:44.637 --> 01:45.772
- THANKS, TIMMY.

01:45.839 --> 01:48.775
YOU'RE PRETTY GROOVY YOURSELF.

01:51.344 --> 01:52.645
- AW, COME ON, TIMMY.

01:52.712 --> 01:54.948
YOUR DAD'S
NOT THAT DANGEROUS.

01:55.014 --> 01:57.183
- AT LEAST NOT TO US
BECAUSE WE'RE IMMORTAL.

01:57.250 --> 01:58.751
- OH, TIMMY?

01:58.818 --> 02:00.753
- AM I DEAD?

02:00.820 --> 02:02.789
- CHECK OUT THE EXTREMELY
CHALLENGING CAMPGROUND

02:02.856 --> 02:04.257
WE'RE GOING TO.

02:04.324 --> 02:06.593
WE'LL BE LUCKY TO COME BACK
WITH OUR SANITY INTACT.

02:06.659 --> 02:09.095
- "FAULT LINE STATE PARK.

02:09.162 --> 02:11.464
"IF YOU HAVE A BAD TIME,
IT'S NOT OUR FAULT.

02:11.531 --> 02:13.433
UNLESS THERE'S
ANOTHER EARTHQUAKE."

02:13.500 --> 02:15.935
DAD, THIS PLACE
SOUNDS DANGEROUS.

02:16.002 --> 02:18.171
- OH, THE EARTHQUAKES
AREN'T THAT BAD.

02:18.238 --> 02:19.806
IT'S THE VICIOUS,
INBRED MOUNTAIN MEN

02:19.873 --> 02:20.874
I'D BE WORRIED ABOUT.

02:20.940 --> 02:22.308
- DAD, DO WE REALLY HAVE

02:22.375 --> 02:23.576
TO GO CAMPING THIS YEAR?

02:23.643 --> 02:25.245
- IT'S A SQUIRRELY SCOUTS
TRADITION.

02:25.311 --> 02:27.680
BESIDES, IF I DRIVE A GROUP
OF BOYS TO THE MOVIES

02:27.747 --> 02:29.115
IN THIS OUTFIT,
THEY'LL ARREST ME.

02:29.182 --> 02:30.850
- OKAY.
EXCUSE ME, DAD.

02:30.917 --> 02:32.385
GUYS, YOU GOTTA SAVE ME.

02:32.452 --> 02:34.153
WE WON'T SURVIVE IF MY DAD
IS TROOP LEADER.

02:34.220 --> 02:36.623
I WISH SOMEONE MORE RESPONSIBLE
WAS IN CHARGE.

02:36.689 --> 02:38.391
- YOU HAVE TO BE
MORE SPECIFIC.

02:38.458 --> 02:40.159
EVEN THE VICIOUS,
INBRED MOUNTAIN MEN

02:40.226 --> 02:41.961
ARE MORE RESPONSIBLE
THAN YOUR DAD.

02:42.028 --> 02:43.296
- AH, LET'S SEE.

02:43.363 --> 02:45.765
WHO'S THE MOST RESPONSIBLE
PERSON I KNOW?

02:45.832 --> 02:46.933
- HEY, TURNER.

02:47.000 --> 02:48.201
JUST RISKED MY LIFE
TO SAVE TIMMY

02:48.268 --> 02:49.335
FROM A FRAYED POWER LINE

02:49.402 --> 02:50.670
THAT ALMOST SWUNG
INTO HIS ROOM.

02:50.737 --> 02:51.771
NO NEED TO THANK ME.

02:51.838 --> 02:53.806
I LIVE TO BE RESPONSIBLE.

02:53.873 --> 02:55.441
- YOU MONSTER!

02:55.508 --> 02:58.044
YOU'RE STEAMING UP THE WINDOW
WITH YOUR HOT DINKLEBREATH!

02:58.111 --> 03:00.380
- [yelps]

03:00.446 --> 03:01.681
- THAT'S IT!

03:01.748 --> 03:06.553
I WISH MR. DINKLEBERG
WAS MY TROOP LEADER.

03:06.619 --> 03:08.421
- THERE YOU ARE, SON.

03:08.488 --> 03:10.456
IF YOU'RE FINISHED TALKING
TO YOURSELF BEHIND THE DOOR,

03:10.523 --> 03:11.457
WE CAN GO CAMPING.

03:11.524 --> 03:13.426
OH, TIMMY, I LOVE BEING

03:13.493 --> 03:14.827
YOUR SQUIRRELY SCOUT LEADER.

03:14.894 --> 03:16.930
- UH, MAYBE WE SHOULD
JUST WAIT A FEW SECONDS

03:16.996 --> 03:19.165
IN CASE WE GET
SOME SURPRISING NEWS.

03:19.232 --> 03:20.667
[phone rings]

03:20.733 --> 03:23.169
- HELLO.
WHAT?

03:23.236 --> 03:25.538
I'M BEING REPLACED
AS THE SQUIRRELY SCOUT LEADER?

03:25.605 --> 03:27.607
THAT IS SURPRISING NEWS.

03:27.674 --> 03:29.676
[sadly]
BY WHO?

03:29.742 --> 03:30.977
- HI, TURNER.

03:31.044 --> 03:32.211
I'M THE NEW SCOUT LEADER.

03:32.278 --> 03:34.347
- DINKLEBERG.

03:34.414 --> 03:35.582
NO!

03:35.648 --> 03:37.150
NO, TIMMY!

03:37.216 --> 03:39.919
I HAD A HORRIBLE DREAM THAT
CANDY TASTED LIKE VEGETABLES.

03:39.986 --> 03:42.288
ALSO, DINKLEBERG REPLACED ME
AS THE SCOUT LEADER.

03:42.355 --> 03:44.891
- THAT WAS NO DREAM, TURNER.
I HAVE REPLACED YOU.

03:44.958 --> 03:46.225
CARE FOR A ZUCCHINI LOLLIPOP?

03:46.292 --> 03:47.260
- NO!

03:47.327 --> 03:49.462
MY NIGHTMARES ARE REAL!

03:49.529 --> 03:50.863
GAH!
- OKAY.

03:50.930 --> 03:53.566
LET'S GO CAMPING.

03:53.633 --> 03:55.969
[all cheer]

03:56.035 --> 03:57.604
- OKAY, CAMPERS.

03:57.670 --> 04:00.139
SQUIRRELY SCOUT CREDO,
TEN-HUT.

04:00.206 --> 04:02.241
all: WE ARE
LITTLE SQUIRRELY SCOUTS.

04:02.308 --> 04:04.177
WE LIKE TO HOARD OUR NUTS.

04:04.243 --> 04:06.346
WE CLIMB UP TREES
AND SKIN OUR KNEES

04:06.412 --> 04:08.448
AND SHAKE
OUR SQUIRRELY BUTTS.

04:08.514 --> 04:10.116
- [retches]

04:10.183 --> 04:12.352
IT'S HARD TO KEEP NUTS IN
YOUR MOUTH WHEN YOU'RE CRYING.

04:12.418 --> 04:13.886
- IT'S GONNA BE OKAY, DAD.

04:13.953 --> 04:16.154
YOU MAY NOT
BE TROOP LEADER ANYMORE,

04:16.221 --> 04:18.190
BUT AT LEAST
THE SQUIRRELY SCOUT ASSOCIATION

04:18.257 --> 04:20.093
SAID IT WAS OKAY
FOR YOU TO COME WITH US.

04:20.159 --> 04:23.763
- SURE, AS A JUNIOR SCOUT,
WHO HAS TO STAY AWAY FROM FIRE

04:23.830 --> 04:25.531
AND SHARP OBJECTS
AND CHILDREN.

04:25.598 --> 04:26.733
WHERE'S THE FUN IN THAT?

04:26.799 --> 04:30.269
OH, MY TINY UNIFORM HURTS!

04:30.336 --> 04:31.604
- I LOVE GOING CAMPING.

04:31.671 --> 04:33.740
THERE'S NOTHING
LIKE LIVING OFF THE LAMB,

04:33.806 --> 04:35.675
SLEEPING UNDER THE STAIRS.

04:35.742 --> 04:38.044
- COSMO, IT'S LIVING
OFF THE LAND

04:38.111 --> 04:40.113
AND SLEEPING
UNDER THE STARS.

04:40.179 --> 04:43.149
- OH, THEN I PACKED STAIRS
AND A LAMB FOR NOTHING.

04:43.216 --> 04:45.084
[lamb bleats]

04:51.357 --> 04:53.826
- THIS DOESN'T LOOK
LIKE FAULT LINE STATE PARK.

04:53.893 --> 04:55.528
- OH, IT'S NOT, TIMMY.

04:55.595 --> 04:56.929
WELCOME TO SAFETY CANYON,

04:56.996 --> 04:58.231
WHERE THERE IS NO CANYON

04:58.297 --> 05:00.199
BECAUSE THAT WOULD
BE TOO DANGEROUS.

05:00.266 --> 05:03.469
- GUYS, THIS PLACE
IS AWESOME.

05:03.536 --> 05:05.304
I DEFINITELY MADE
THE RIGHT DECISION

05:05.371 --> 05:07.573
BY REPLACING MY DAD
WITH MR. DINKLEBERG.

05:07.640 --> 05:09.842
I AM SO HAPPY!

05:09.909 --> 05:11.477
- I'M SO SAD.

05:11.544 --> 05:13.479
AND NOT JUST BECAUSE I SAT
ON THIS PORCUPINE.

05:13.546 --> 05:16.215
[yelps]
I MISS BEING TROOP LEADER!

05:16.282 --> 05:18.284
[sobs]

05:18.351 --> 05:21.020
- THEN AGAIN, MAYBE I DIDN'T
MAKE THE RIGHT DECISION.

05:21.087 --> 05:23.156
- OH, TIMMY,
YOU JUST NEED TO RELAX

05:23.222 --> 05:24.857
AND TAKE IN THE FRESH HARE.

05:24.924 --> 05:26.693
[sniffs and sighs]

05:26.759 --> 05:29.062
AW, YUCK,
I NEED A FRESHER HARE.

05:29.128 --> 05:31.264
THIS ONE SMELLS
LIKE DIRT AND CARROTS.

05:31.330 --> 05:32.398
[yelps]

05:32.465 --> 05:33.433
OKAY.

05:33.499 --> 05:35.301
I AM STARTING
TO HATE CAMPING.

05:35.368 --> 05:37.103
- WANDA, MAYBE I WAS WRONG

05:37.170 --> 05:38.838
TO MAKE MR. DINKLEBERG
THE SCOUT LEADER.

05:38.905 --> 05:40.673
I BROKE MY DAD'S HEART.

05:40.740 --> 05:42.508
I WISH--
- OKAY, KIDS.

05:42.575 --> 05:45.878
I SET UP OUR CAMPSITE.

05:45.945 --> 05:47.580
- YOU WISH WHAT, TIMMY?

05:47.647 --> 05:51.451
- I WISH I WAS THE FIRST
IN LINE FOR THE FERRIS WHEEL!

05:51.517 --> 05:53.553
[all cheer]

05:53.619 --> 05:54.821
- OKAY, CAMPERS.

05:54.887 --> 05:57.356
TIME TO GO
ON A SUPER SAFE HIKE.

05:57.423 --> 05:59.759
- WHENEVER WE GO
HIKING WITH MR. TURNER,

05:59.826 --> 06:01.994
WE GET LOST
AND MAULED BY A BEAR.

06:02.061 --> 06:03.062
- OH, DON'T WORRY.

06:03.129 --> 06:04.497
I HAVE A G.P.S.,
WHICH IS LINKED

06:04.564 --> 06:06.599
TO A SATELLITE THAT I BUILT
OUT OF LEFTOVER PARTS

06:06.666 --> 06:07.734
FROM THE FERRIS WHEEL.

06:07.800 --> 06:09.802
- [scoffs]
NO TRUE CAMP LEADER

06:09.869 --> 06:11.170
USES TECHNOLOGY.

06:11.237 --> 06:14.006
I'LL NAVIGATE THE TRAIL
WITH MY ROCK COMPASS.

06:14.073 --> 06:16.743
OOH, BUT FIRST I'LL FILL
THE POCKETS OF MY TINY PANTS

06:16.809 --> 06:20.847
WITH RAW HAMBURGER
FOR GOOD LUCK.

06:20.913 --> 06:23.049
[growling]
[screams]

06:23.116 --> 06:25.885
HAMBURGER IS NOT GOOD LUCK!

06:25.952 --> 06:27.754
- OKAY, SQUIRRELY SCOUTS.

06:27.820 --> 06:29.555
TIME FOR CANOEING.

06:29.622 --> 06:31.724
- WHEN WE WENT CANOEING
WITH MR. TURNER,

06:31.791 --> 06:33.659
WE HIT AN ICEBERG AND SANK.

06:33.726 --> 06:35.595
- DON'T WORRY.
NO ICEBERGS HERE.

06:35.661 --> 06:38.197
I HAD THE LAKE HEATED
TO A SOOTHING 82 DEGREES

06:38.264 --> 06:39.532
AND FILLED IT WITH COCOA.

06:39.599 --> 06:41.934
NOW HOP INTO
YOUR FLUFFY MARSHMALLOW BOATS.

06:42.001 --> 06:43.035
- WHOO-HOO!

06:43.102 --> 06:44.370
COME ON, DAD.

06:44.437 --> 06:46.239
DAD?

06:46.305 --> 06:48.508
- JUST GO WITH DINKLEBERG,
TIMMY.

06:48.574 --> 06:51.577
AFTER ALL, HE'S
YOUR FAVORITEST TROOP LEADER.

06:51.644 --> 06:53.379
I'M GONNA SHOOT THE RAPIDS
IN THIS CANOE

06:53.446 --> 06:54.947
I MADE
OUT OF RUSTY MACHETES.

06:55.014 --> 06:56.682
I THINK
I'LL TAKE THIS RIVER

06:56.749 --> 06:58.584
WITH A SKULL
AND CROSSBONES SIGN NEXT TO IT.

06:58.651 --> 07:01.554
THERE WAS ONE JUST LIKE THIS
ON THE ICEBERG WE HIT LAST YEAR.

07:01.621 --> 07:02.855
SEE?

07:02.922 --> 07:05.758
I'M HAVING
MY OWN SUPER SAFE SCOUTING FUN.

07:05.825 --> 07:07.126
[screams]

07:07.193 --> 07:08.961
I'M GRIPPED WITH TERROR!

07:09.028 --> 07:10.329
- FUN FACT, SCOUTS.

07:10.396 --> 07:12.832
THIS PARK HAS THE TALLEST
WATERFALL ON THE PLANET.

07:12.899 --> 07:15.067
YOU CAN EVEN SEE IT
FROM SPACE.

07:15.134 --> 07:16.269
- [screams]

07:16.335 --> 07:20.807
IF YOU CAN SEE ME FROM SPACE,
HELP!

07:20.873 --> 07:23.743
[all cheer]

07:23.810 --> 07:26.946
- YOU'RE THE BEST SCOUT LEADER
EVER, MR. DINKLEBERG.

07:27.013 --> 07:29.482
- YEAH, WHEN WE PLAYED
VOLLEYBALL WITH MR. TURNER,

07:29.549 --> 07:31.918
WE USUALLY HIT AN ICEBERG--
OOF!

07:31.984 --> 07:33.586
- I DON'T EVEN KNOW
HOW THAT'S POSSIBLE.

07:33.653 --> 07:36.923
NOW COME SIT DOWN AND ENJOY
SOME DELICIOUS DINKLEBURGERS.

07:36.989 --> 07:38.624
THEY'RE MADE OUT OF LOBSTER.

07:38.691 --> 07:41.093
- BUT I'M ALLERGIC
TO SHELLFISH.

07:41.160 --> 07:43.563
- THAT'S OKAY,
IT'S MARSHMALLOW LOBSTER.

07:43.629 --> 07:46.933
[all cheer]

07:46.999 --> 07:48.668
- THEY DON'T NEED ME.

07:48.734 --> 07:50.303
I'M JUST GONNA SLINK
INTO THE WOODS

07:50.369 --> 07:52.905
AND LIVE IN SHAME
FOR THE REST OF MY DAYS.

07:52.972 --> 07:57.176
OR AT LEAST UNTIL MONDAY,
WHEN I HAVE TO GO BACK TO WORK.

07:57.243 --> 08:00.179
[somber music]

08:00.246 --> 08:02.181
♪ ♪

08:02.248 --> 08:05.518
- DAD, I BROUGHT YOU
A DINKLEBURGER.

08:05.585 --> 08:06.953
DAD?

08:07.019 --> 08:10.056
"DEAR SON, DINKLEBERG IS
A BETTER SCOUT LEADER THAN ME.

08:10.122 --> 08:13.359
"THE SQUIRRELY SCOUT ASSOCIATION
WAS RIGHT TO REPLACE ME.

08:13.426 --> 08:16.796
"YOU'LL NEVER HAVE TO LOOK
AT MY SORRY FACE AGAIN.

08:16.863 --> 08:18.564
SEE YOU MONDAY.
LOVE, DAD."

08:18.631 --> 08:20.132
OH, NO, SPARKY.

08:20.199 --> 08:22.335
MY DAD CAN'T SURVIVE ALONE
IN THE WOODS.

08:22.401 --> 08:24.470
HE CAN BARELY SURVIVE ALONE
IN OUR HOUSE.

08:24.537 --> 08:26.706
USE YOUR CANINE SENSES
TO TRACK HIM DOWN.

08:26.772 --> 08:28.107
- YOU GOT IT, TIMMY.

08:28.174 --> 08:31.577
I'LL DO
WHAT ALL DOGS DO.

08:33.246 --> 08:36.982
[sniffs]

08:37.049 --> 08:39.986
[rock music plays]

08:40.052 --> 08:45.491
♪ ♪

08:45.558 --> 08:47.693
- A DOG
HIJACKED OUR BUS.

08:47.760 --> 08:48.928
- THAT'S OKAY, KIDS.

08:48.995 --> 08:53.633
I BROUGHT JETPACKS.

08:53.699 --> 08:56.869
[growling]

08:56.936 --> 08:58.504
- I FEEL TERRIBLE.

08:58.571 --> 09:01.507
I'VE LET TIMMY DOWN, AND THERE
ARE FIRE ANTS ON THIS STUMP.

09:01.574 --> 09:02.942
I HOPE
I DON'T START HALLUCINATING

09:03.009 --> 09:04.477
FROM SADNESS
AND FIRE ANT VENOM.

09:04.543 --> 09:07.513
[horn honks]

09:07.580 --> 09:09.782
OOH, A DOG DRIVING A BUS.

09:09.849 --> 09:10.917
NOTHING WEIRD THERE.

09:10.983 --> 09:12.485
- HEY, TIMMY'S DAD.

09:12.551 --> 09:13.886
- A TALKING DOG.

09:13.953 --> 09:16.255
NOW I KNOW
I'M HALLUCINATING.

09:16.322 --> 09:18.524
THE VENOM HAS GONE STRAIGHT
FROM MY BUTT TO MY BRAIN.

09:18.591 --> 09:20.893
- TIMMY SENT ME.
HE'S WORRIED ABOUT YOU.

09:20.960 --> 09:24.430
- OH, TIMMY DOESN'T NEED ME,
FIGMENT OF MY IMAGINATION.

09:24.497 --> 09:27.667
HE'S HAVING THE TIME
OF HIS LIFE WITH DINKLEBERG.

09:27.733 --> 09:28.901
- AHH, HELP!

09:28.968 --> 09:30.503
DAD, SAVE ME!

09:30.569 --> 09:32.471
- OOH!
TIMMY'S IN DANGER.

09:32.538 --> 09:34.273
I'D RESCUE HIM,
BUT I'D ONLY MESS IT UP.

09:34.340 --> 09:35.741
DINKLEBERG CAN SAVE HIM.

09:35.808 --> 09:38.077
- AHH, I CAN'T SAVE HIM!

09:38.144 --> 09:39.679
- YOU CAN DO IT,
TIMMY'S DAD.

09:39.745 --> 09:41.013
YOU'RE TIMMY'S DAD.

09:41.080 --> 09:43.049
- THAT KIND OF WISDOM
IS HARD TO ARGUE WITH.

09:43.115 --> 09:44.750
COME ON,
DOG THAT ISN'T HERE.

09:44.817 --> 09:46.385
DRIVE ME BACK TO CAMP.

09:46.452 --> 09:49.388
[rock music plays]

09:49.455 --> 09:53.025
♪ ♪

09:53.092 --> 09:55.027
- [whimpers]

09:55.094 --> 09:58.564
[all growling]

09:58.631 --> 10:01.400
- STAY AWAY
FROM MY SON, BEAR!

10:01.467 --> 10:03.202
I MAY NOT BE ABLE
TO CAMP, CANOE,

10:03.269 --> 10:04.704
OR SURVIVE
IN MY OWN HOUSE,

10:04.770 --> 10:06.806
BUT I CAN GET
ON AN IMAGINARY BUS

10:06.872 --> 10:07.974
WITH A MADE-UP DOG!

10:08.040 --> 10:09.308
[confused growls]

10:09.375 --> 10:10.576
- GREAT JOB, DAD.

10:10.643 --> 10:12.611
YOUR GIBBERISH
CONFUSED THE BEARS.

10:12.678 --> 10:14.413
- YEAH, IT CONFUSED ME TOO.

10:14.480 --> 10:16.015
WHAT WAS I SAYING?
OH, RIGHT!

10:16.082 --> 10:18.150
NATURE'S PINATA,
DO YOUR STUFF!

10:18.217 --> 10:21.454
DUCK, TIMMY!

10:21.520 --> 10:25.791
[bears growl]
[bees buzz]

10:25.858 --> 10:27.460
[all cheer]

10:27.526 --> 10:29.962
- YOU DID IT, DAD.
YOU SAVED US.

10:30.029 --> 10:31.297
- GOOD JOB, TURNER.

10:31.364 --> 10:33.032
YOU'RE A HERO
AND MORE DESERVING

10:33.099 --> 10:35.234
TO BE A SQUIRRELY SCOUT
TROOP LEADER THAN I AM.

10:35.301 --> 10:37.003
- YOU TAKE THAT BACK,
DINKLEBERG!

10:37.069 --> 10:38.604
OH, WAIT.

10:38.671 --> 10:40.272
ANYWAY, I DON'T NEED
TO BE A SCOUT LEADER

10:40.339 --> 10:42.408
AS LONG AS YOU'RE PROUD
OF ME, SON.

10:42.475 --> 10:43.976
- I WAS ALWAYS PROUD
OF YOU, DAD.

10:44.043 --> 10:46.846
SURE, YOU NEVER
DO ANYTHING RIGHT.

10:46.912 --> 10:48.347
BUT YOU NEVER STOP TRYING.

10:48.414 --> 10:50.049
THREE CHEERS
FOR MY DAD!

10:50.116 --> 10:52.118
all: HIP HIP HOORAY!

10:52.184 --> 10:54.120
HIP HIP HOORAY!

10:54.186 --> 10:55.921
HIP HIP HOORAY!

10:55.988 --> 10:56.922
[bird squawks]

10:56.989 --> 10:58.057
- [screams]

10:58.124 --> 10:59.725
I'VE BEEN SNATCHED
BY A HAWK!

10:59.792 --> 11:01.727
- WELL, SPORT,
LOOKS LIKE YOUR DAD'S

11:01.794 --> 11:04.196
NOT SUCH A BAD SCOUT LEADER
AFTER ALL.

11:04.263 --> 11:05.631
- YOU'RE RIGHT, WANDA.

11:05.698 --> 11:07.533
AS SOON AS THAT HAWK
LETS HIM GO,

11:07.600 --> 11:10.636
I'M GONNA UNDO MY WISH
AND MAKE HIM SCOUT LEADER AGAIN.

11:10.703 --> 11:12.505
HEY, WHERE'S COSMO?

11:12.571 --> 11:15.007
- UP HERE, GUYS.

11:15.074 --> 11:16.876
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING
UP THERE?

11:16.942 --> 11:19.445
- DUH, I'M ROOFING IT.

11:19.512 --> 11:20.846
- THAT'S "ROUGHING IT."

11:20.913 --> 11:22.481
- SAID THE CITY SLICKER.

11:22.548 --> 11:25.418
- CURSE YOU, DINKLEBERG!

11:25.484 --> 11:27.119
[yelps]
AN ICEBERG!

11:27.186 --> 11:28.654
NOW I'M SINKING!

11:45.571 --> 11:46.906
- HEY, SPARKY.

11:46.972 --> 11:48.240
WANNA PLAY FETCH?

11:48.307 --> 11:50.042
- IF YOU'RE UP FOR IT, SURE.

11:50.109 --> 11:52.011
FETCH!

11:52.078 --> 11:53.012
[crash]

11:53.079 --> 11:54.113
YAY!

11:54.180 --> 11:56.048
I BROKE SOMETHING
ON MY FIRST TRY!

11:56.115 --> 11:57.850
I'M GOOD AT FETCH!

11:57.917 --> 11:59.418
- MY PARENTS'LL FLIP.

11:59.485 --> 12:01.654
- WE GOTTA GET IT BACK.

12:01.720 --> 12:04.457
- WHOA, THIS ATTIC
IS A MESS.

12:04.523 --> 12:05.925
WE'LL NEVER FIND THE BALL.

12:05.991 --> 12:07.793
- OOH, A LAMP.

12:07.860 --> 12:10.729
MAYBE THE BALL
FELL IN HERE.

12:10.796 --> 12:12.431
[grunts]

12:12.498 --> 12:14.133
OOH, DARK IN HERE.

12:14.200 --> 12:15.768
IRONIC FOR A LAMP.

12:15.835 --> 12:16.902
- GEE, SPORT.

12:16.969 --> 12:19.271
YOUR MOM HAS
A LOT OF BALL GOWNS.

12:19.338 --> 12:21.006
- I HEAR THE RUSTLE
OF TAFFETA.

12:21.073 --> 12:25.010
WHO'S PLAYING
WITH MY BALL GOWNS?

12:27.780 --> 12:29.115
- [groans]

12:29.181 --> 12:31.717
- TIMMY, WHAT ARE YOU
DOING IN MY DRESS-UP ROOM?

12:31.784 --> 12:32.952
I MEAN, MAN CAVE.

12:33.018 --> 12:34.353
- MAN CAVE?

12:34.420 --> 12:35.754
THERE'S ONLY
A FOLDING CHAIR,

12:35.821 --> 12:38.791
AN A.M. RADIO,
AND SOME COUGH DROPS.

12:38.858 --> 12:40.726
- I'D HAVE
A BETTER MAN CAVE

12:40.793 --> 12:43.562
IF I DIDN'T HAVE SO MANY
GROWN-UP RESPONSIBILITIES.

12:43.629 --> 12:46.432
[sobs]
B-B-BUT IT'S OKAY.

12:46.499 --> 12:49.768
YOU AND--AND YOUR MOTHER
AND--AND ALL THE MONEY YOU NEED

12:49.835 --> 12:52.271
ARE VERY IMPORTANT TO ME.

12:52.338 --> 12:56.275
- OKAY, WELL, I'M JUST GONNA
AWKWARDLY HEAD BACK TO MY ROOM,

12:56.342 --> 12:59.812
SHOULD ANYONE
BE LOOKING FOR ME!

13:01.413 --> 13:05.251
- AND NOW BACK TO OUR PROGRAM,
<i>TODAY'S BALL GOWNS.</i>

13:05.317 --> 13:06.719
- THIS IS THE MANLY LIFE.

13:06.785 --> 13:07.753
AAH!

13:07.820 --> 13:09.255
OH, WHO AM I KIDDING?

13:09.321 --> 13:10.823
HOW WILL I EVER GET
ENOUGH MONEY

13:10.890 --> 13:14.226
TO TURN THIS PATHETIC ATTIC
INTO A REAL MAN CAVE?

13:14.293 --> 13:15.661
- DOES ANYONE HAVE
A COUGH DROP?

13:15.728 --> 13:20.266
IT'S DUSTY IN HERE.

13:20.332 --> 13:22.168
[grunts]

13:22.234 --> 13:24.336
- OOH!
A GENIE IN A LAMP.

13:24.403 --> 13:26.005
MAYBE HE CAN LEND ME
THE MONEY.

13:26.071 --> 13:27.840
- I'M A GENIE?

13:27.907 --> 13:30.075
- WELL, THE ONLY THINGS
THAT FALL OUT OF LAMPS

13:30.142 --> 13:31.677
ARE GENIES
AND DEAD SILVERFISH.

13:31.744 --> 13:34.613
AND DEAD SILVERFISH CAN'T
MAKE YOUR DREAMS COME TRUE.

13:34.680 --> 13:37.116
UGH, LEARNED THAT
THE HARD WAY.

13:37.183 --> 13:38.617
SO YOU MUST BE A GENIE.

13:38.684 --> 13:39.685
GRANT ME A WISH!

13:39.752 --> 13:40.786
GRANT! GRANT!

13:40.853 --> 13:42.988
- SO MY NAME
IS "GRANT" THEN.

13:43.055 --> 13:45.124
"ONE WISH COMING UP,"
GRANT SAID.

13:45.191 --> 13:46.358
- WAIT A MINUTE.

13:46.425 --> 13:47.927
YOU HAVE A WAND?

13:47.993 --> 13:50.462
YOU MUST BE PART WITCH,
PART GENIE.

13:50.529 --> 13:52.364
[gasps]
YOU'RE A MAGIC WEENIE!

13:52.431 --> 13:54.867
- WAIT A MINUTE.
WHERE'S COSMO?

13:54.934 --> 13:55.868
OH, NO.

13:55.935 --> 13:57.636
I HOPE MY DAD DOESN'T FIND HIM.

13:57.703 --> 14:00.573
- I FOUND A MAGIC WEENIE!

14:00.639 --> 14:02.741
- OH, NO.
WE'VE GOTTA GET UP THERE.

14:02.808 --> 14:04.677
- OH, I DON'T KNOW, TIMMY.

14:04.743 --> 14:07.846
YOUR FATHER AND COSMO
IN THE SAME ROOM TOGETHER?

14:07.913 --> 14:11.850
IT MIGHT BE SAFER TO JUST
PACK UP AND MOVE TO MEXICO.

14:11.917 --> 14:13.085
- MEXICO?

14:13.152 --> 14:14.920
I KNOW A GUY DOWN THERE
WHO CAN SET US UP.

14:14.987 --> 14:19.592
- LET'S SEE WHAT'S GOING ON
IN THE ATTIC FIRST.

14:19.658 --> 14:21.694
- SO WHAT DOES
A WEENIE DO?

14:21.760 --> 14:23.729
- YOU HAVE TO GRANT ME
THREE WISHES.

14:23.796 --> 14:25.698
AND BY THREE,
I MEAN A GAZILLION.

14:25.764 --> 14:31.570
MY FIRST WISH IS TO TURN
THIS ATTIC INTO A REAL MAN CAVE.

14:31.637 --> 14:34.740
[bear growls]

14:34.807 --> 14:36.909
- [shrieks]

14:36.976 --> 14:38.544
AHH! LOSE THE BEAR.

14:38.611 --> 14:39.912
HE'LL TEAR UP MY BALL GOWNS.

14:39.979 --> 14:43.215
JUST GIVE ME
AWESOME, MANLY THINGS.

14:45.584 --> 14:46.685
COOL!

14:46.752 --> 14:48.187
FLAT SCREEN TV!

14:48.254 --> 14:50.856
OOH! A FANCY BOWL
FOR MY COUGH DROPS.

14:50.923 --> 14:54.727
OH! AND A VIBRATING CHAIR
THAT REQUIRES QUARTERS.

14:54.793 --> 14:57.263
EVERYONE KNOWS QUARTERS
ARE THE MANLIEST

14:57.329 --> 14:59.732
OF ALL COINS.

15:01.634 --> 15:06.038
[quivery]
THIS IS THE LIFE, GRANT.

15:06.105 --> 15:07.873
[screams]

15:07.940 --> 15:10.876
- COSMO, YOU'RE NOT SUPPOSED
TO BE TALKING TO MY DAD.

15:10.943 --> 15:12.177
- WHAT'S A COSMO?

15:12.244 --> 15:14.046
I'M A WEENIE,
AND MY NAME IS GRANT.

15:14.113 --> 15:16.382
- OH, I THINK
HE HAS AMNESIA.

15:16.448 --> 15:19.685
COSMO, LISTEN TO ME.
YOU ARE NOT A WEENIE.

15:19.752 --> 15:20.886
YOU'RE A FAIRY.

15:20.953 --> 15:22.321
- IF I WAS A FAIRY,

15:22.388 --> 15:24.223
I WOULD BE RULING
OVER A BUNCH OF EGYPTIANS.

15:24.290 --> 15:25.691
- THAT'S A PHARAOH!

15:25.758 --> 15:27.293
OH, FORGET IT.

15:27.359 --> 15:28.727
LET'S JUST HIT HIM
OVER THE HEAD

15:28.794 --> 15:30.396
AND HOPE HE GETS
HIS MEMORY BACK.

15:30.462 --> 15:32.131
- CAN'T WE JUST
TAKE HIM TO A SHRINK?

15:32.197 --> 15:34.233
- "I'LL TAKE YOU
TO A SHRINK,"

15:34.300 --> 15:37.102
GRANT SAID CLEVERLY.

15:40.139 --> 15:41.907
- OH, NO!
COSMO SHRUNK US DOWN.

15:41.974 --> 15:46.145
WANDA, YOU GOTTA
POOF US BACK TO NORMAL.

15:46.211 --> 15:48.781
- SORRY, SPORT,
BUT WHEN YOU SHRINK A WAND,

15:48.847 --> 15:52.151
YOU ONLY HAVE ENOUGH MAGIC
TO DO SILLY PARLOR TRICKS.

15:54.586 --> 15:57.656
OH, A LITTLE WATER
WON'T HURT YOU.

16:00.392 --> 16:02.461
[all scream]

16:02.528 --> 16:04.363
- WE'RE GONNA DROWN.

16:04.430 --> 16:06.999
SPARKY, HELP!

16:10.903 --> 16:11.870
- [giggles]

16:11.937 --> 16:14.139
- HEY, HONEY.
GREAT NEWS.

16:14.206 --> 16:17.509
I HAVE A MAGIC GRANT,
WHO GAVE ME THIS VIBRATING CHAIR

16:17.576 --> 16:19.712
AND AN ENDLESS SUPPLY
OF QUARTERS.

16:19.778 --> 16:22.815
- HOW MANY OF THOSE COUGH DROPS
HAVE YOU HAD, DEAR?

16:22.881 --> 16:25.217
ANYWAY, YOU'RE GONNA BE LATE
FOR WORK.

16:25.284 --> 16:26.885
- IF ONLY
I DIDN'T HAVE TO GO.

16:26.952 --> 16:28.120
[gasps]
WAIT A MINUTE.

16:28.187 --> 16:30.489
THE WEENIE,
HE COULD DRIVE ME TO WORK!

16:30.556 --> 16:32.558
BETTER YET,
WE COULD STOP FOR WAFFLES!

16:32.624 --> 16:35.728
- OR I COULD MAKE IT
SO YOU NEVER HAVE TO WORK AGAIN.

16:35.794 --> 16:36.895
- COULD WE STILL
HAVE WAFFLES?

16:36.962 --> 16:41.567
- "DONE," GRANT SAID,
WAFFLE-Y.

16:41.633 --> 16:45.003
NOW YOU NEVER
HAVE TO WORK AGAIN.

16:45.070 --> 16:47.106
[phone rings]

16:47.172 --> 16:49.675
- OOH, IT'S MY BOSS,
MR. ED LEADLY.

16:49.742 --> 16:51.143
- YOU'RE FIRED, TURNER.

16:51.210 --> 16:52.911
- THANK YOU,
MR. ED LEADLY.

16:52.978 --> 16:55.748
THIS IS THE BEST DAY
OF MY LIFE!

16:55.814 --> 16:58.717
GREAT NEWS, HONEY.
I WAS FIRED!

16:58.784 --> 17:00.853
DON'T WORRY, WE'LL JUST PAY
OUR BILLS WITH QUARTERS.

17:00.919 --> 17:02.654
- THAT'S NICE, DEAR.

17:02.721 --> 17:04.589
BUT YOU STILL
HAVE TO TAKE OUT THE TRASH.

17:04.656 --> 17:07.425
- GAH, I HATE DOING CHORES.

17:07.492 --> 17:09.694
GRANT, CAN YOU
MAKE MY WIFE DISAPPEAR?

17:09.762 --> 17:11.262
- ISN'T THAT ILLEGAL?

17:11.329 --> 17:13.198
- NOT IF YOU MAKE
THE POLICE DISAPPEAR.

17:13.265 --> 17:15.166
- "I SEE WHERE YOU'RE GOING
WITH THIS,"

17:15.233 --> 17:16.969
GRANT SAID NERVOUSLY.

17:17.035 --> 17:18.637
UM, HOW ABOUT
I JUST MAKE IT

17:18.704 --> 17:22.875
SO YOU NEVER HAVE
TO TAKE OUT THE TRASH AGAIN?

17:25.676 --> 17:26.744
TA-DA!

17:26.811 --> 17:28.414
NOW YOUR HOUSE
IS THE CITY DUMP,

17:28.480 --> 17:30.883
SO YOU CAN LEAVE
YOUR TRASH WHERE IT IS.

17:30.949 --> 17:31.984
- YAY!

17:32.050 --> 17:33.752
HOW COULD THIS DAY
GET ANY BETTER?

17:33.819 --> 17:36.255
- HONEY,
LOOK AT ALL THIS CASH!

17:36.321 --> 17:39.491
PEOPLE ARE PAYING US TO DUMP
THEIR GARBAGE AT OUR HOUSE.

17:39.558 --> 17:42.127
WE'RE MAKING MORE MONEY
THAN YOU EVER DID

17:42.194 --> 17:44.129
AT YOUR DEAD END PENCIL JOB.

17:44.196 --> 17:45.364
[truck beeps]

17:45.431 --> 17:47.933
OOH, A DUMP TRUCK
FILLED WITH OLD TOILETS.

17:48.000 --> 17:50.202
WE'RE GONNA BE FLUSH
WITH CASH.

17:50.269 --> 17:51.570
GET IT?

17:51.637 --> 17:54.273
EH, I DON'T GET IT,
BUT I LOVE THAT WOMAN.

17:54.339 --> 17:57.276
AND SHE'LL LOVE ME EVEN MORE
WHEN I WISH FOR HUGE BICEPS.

18:01.180 --> 18:02.581
[yelps]

18:02.648 --> 18:03.916
BE RIGHT BACK, GRANT.

18:03.982 --> 18:05.284
I'M GONNA GO SHOW DINKLEBERG

18:05.350 --> 18:08.086
MY BUFF BICEPS
AND MY ROLL OF MANLY QUARTERS.

18:08.153 --> 18:10.689
[truck beeps]

18:10.756 --> 18:14.059
- AAH!

18:14.126 --> 18:15.427
- THIS IS A NIGHTMARE.

18:15.494 --> 18:17.930
WE'RE TINY, AND MY HOUSE
IS FULL OF GARBAGE.

18:17.996 --> 18:19.398
- TIMMY, FOCUS.

18:19.465 --> 18:22.000
THIS IS OUR CHANCE
TO BONK COSMO ON THE HEAD,

18:22.067 --> 18:24.403
SO HE GETS
HIS MEMORY BACK.

18:24.470 --> 18:26.772
- SPARKY,
GRAB THAT FRYING PAN.

18:26.839 --> 18:29.675
[heroic music]

18:29.741 --> 18:31.577
- OH, GRANT?

18:31.643 --> 18:36.181
- COMING,
YOUR ROYAL SLAVE DRIVER.

18:36.248 --> 18:37.683
- GUESS WHAT, GRANT.

18:37.749 --> 18:39.384
I'VE GONE MAD
WITH POWER.

18:39.451 --> 18:41.186
I HAVE A WHOLE LIST
OF DEMANDS.

18:41.253 --> 18:42.521
SOME OF THEM MIGHT
BE A LITTLE CRAZY

18:42.588 --> 18:45.357
BECAUSE ALL THE BLOOD
HAS RUSHED TO MY HEAD.

18:45.424 --> 18:46.792
[gasps]
OH, NO.

18:46.859 --> 18:50.128
HERE COMES MY EVIL NEIGHBOR,
DINKLEBERG.

18:50.195 --> 18:51.163
- HEY, TURNER.

18:51.230 --> 18:52.331
I GOT A MILLION-DOLLAR REWARD

18:52.397 --> 18:54.032
FOR SAVING A CAT
FROM A BURNING HOUSE,

18:54.099 --> 18:55.534
AND I THOUGHT
IT WOULD BE NEIGHBORLY

18:55.601 --> 18:57.035
TO GIVE HALF OF IT TO YOU.

18:57.102 --> 19:01.373
- YOU CONNIVING,
BLACK-HEARTED MONSTER!

19:01.440 --> 19:03.709
I WISH DINKLEBERG
NEVER EXISTED.

19:03.775 --> 19:05.711
- "OKAY,
BUT THERE'S A SMALL CHANCE

19:05.777 --> 19:07.846
THAT COULD ALTER
THE FABRIC OF SPACE AND TIME,"

19:07.913 --> 19:09.314
HE SAID, WAFFLE-Y.

19:09.381 --> 19:11.416
- JUST DO IT!

19:19.191 --> 19:22.628
[monster roars]

19:22.694 --> 19:24.730
[yelps]

19:24.796 --> 19:26.665
CHANGE IT BACK!
CHANGE IT BACK!

19:26.732 --> 19:31.236
OOH, BUT LEAVE MY BICEPS
THE WAY THEY ARE.

19:31.303 --> 19:34.806
- WELL, I HAVE NO MEMORY
OF WHAT JUST HAPPENED.

19:34.873 --> 19:36.508
SPEND YOUR MONEY WISELY,
TURNER.

19:36.575 --> 19:38.644
- I SHOULD BE CAREFUL
ABOUT WHAT I WISH FOR,

19:38.710 --> 19:40.279
OR I MIGHT DESTROY
THE WORLD.

19:40.345 --> 19:41.313
I KNOW!

19:41.380 --> 19:43.015
I WISH THE SUN WAS CLOSER,

19:43.081 --> 19:46.518
SO I CAN BRONZE
MY BEEFY BICEPS.

19:54.860 --> 19:57.162
- MM, NOTHING LIKE
THE SMELL OF HOT GARBAGE

19:57.229 --> 20:00.766
AND ROASTING BICEPS
ON A SUMMER DAY IN JANUARY.

20:00.832 --> 20:03.201
- OH, NO.
WHAT DID MY DAD DO?

20:03.268 --> 20:05.037
WANDA, HOW ARE WE
GONNA STOP THE SUN

20:05.103 --> 20:06.572
FROM INCINERATING
THE EARTH?

20:06.638 --> 20:11.143
- SORRY, TIMMY, BUT ALL I CAN DO
ARE THESE USELESS MAGIC TRICKS.

20:11.209 --> 20:13.111
- WAIT A MINUTE,
THAT'S IT!

20:13.178 --> 20:15.013
WE CAN USE
THIS NEVER-ENDING HANDKERCHIEF

20:15.080 --> 20:18.417
TO SWING OURSELVES
OVER TO COSMO.

20:22.888 --> 20:24.890
[all scream]

20:28.727 --> 20:30.963
I GOTTA SAY,
COSMO'S BRAIN

20:31.029 --> 20:32.598
IS A LOT BIGGER
THAN I THOUGHT IT WOULD BE.

20:32.664 --> 20:35.601
- THAT'S NOT HIS BRAIN.
THAT'S A RAISIN.

20:35.667 --> 20:38.604
HE KEEPS RAISINS IN HIS HEAD
TO PUT ON HIS CEREAL.

20:38.670 --> 20:43.175
- BOY, I COULD GO FOR A BIG BOWL
OF RAISIN BRAIN CEREAL.

20:43.241 --> 20:44.710
[all scream]

20:44.776 --> 20:47.679
- HURRY, WE HAVE TO KICK-START
COSMO'S BRAIN!

20:47.746 --> 20:49.348
- WHICH ONE'S HIS BRAIN?

20:49.414 --> 20:53.852
- OH, JUST KEEP
KICKING RAISINS.

20:53.919 --> 20:55.621
YAH!

20:55.687 --> 20:58.790
[grunting]

20:58.857 --> 21:01.093
- WAIT A MINUTE.
IT'S ALL COMING BACK TO ME.

21:01.159 --> 21:02.527
I'M NOT A WEENIE.

21:02.594 --> 21:05.030
I'M THE PLUCKY BASS PLAYER
IN AN ALL-GIRL BAND.

21:05.097 --> 21:06.865
- [grunts]

21:06.932 --> 21:09.401
- NO, I'M A--
I'M A FAIRY.

21:09.468 --> 21:10.969
AND MY NAME IS COUSCOUS!

21:11.036 --> 21:12.437
- CLOSE ENOUGH.

21:12.504 --> 21:15.374
- COSMO, YOU HAVE TO POOF
EVERYTHING BACK TO NORMAL.

21:15.440 --> 21:18.377
[heroic music]

21:18.443 --> 21:26.385
♪ ♪

21:27.953 --> 21:29.921
PHEW, THAT WAS CLOSE.

21:29.988 --> 21:32.457
COSMO, IT'S GOOD
TO HAVE YOU BACK.

21:32.524 --> 21:33.859
- IT'S GOOD TO BE BACK.

21:33.925 --> 21:36.728
BEING ON TOUR WITH
AN ALL-GIRL BAND IS EXHAUSTING.

21:36.795 --> 21:39.464
STAYING UP LATE,
SHARING MAKEUP TIPS,

21:39.531 --> 21:41.299
HAVING PILLOW FIGHTS
IN OUR UNDERWEAR.

21:41.366 --> 21:44.569
- [sobbing]
OH, GRANT IS GONE.

21:44.636 --> 21:46.705
I MUST HAVE MADE
TOO MANY WISHES.

21:46.772 --> 21:49.341
ALL I HAVE LEFT ARE
THESE EARWAX-COVERED RAISINS

21:49.408 --> 21:51.743
AND $1/2 MILLION
FROM DINKLEBERG.

21:51.810 --> 21:53.845
LIKE THAT'S ANY CONSOLATION.

21:53.912 --> 21:55.914
CURSE YOU, DINKLEBERG!

21:55.981 --> 21:58.950
ME, I GUESS I'LL JUST GO BACK
TO MY PATHETIC MAN CAVE

21:59.017 --> 22:01.920
WITH MY A.M. RADIO
AND EXPIRED COUGH DROPS.

22:01.987 --> 22:05.824
- COSMO, I WANT YOU TO GRANT
MY DAD ONE LAST WISH.

22:05.891 --> 22:08.427
- MY MAN CAVE!

22:08.493 --> 22:11.563
IT'S EVEN BETTER
THAN BEFORE.

22:11.630 --> 22:13.098
- GRANT, YOU'RE BACK!

22:13.165 --> 22:15.400
- YES, BUT NOW,
LIKE ALL WEENIES,

22:15.467 --> 22:18.103
I'M OFF TO THE NORTH POLE
TO FIND ME POT OF GOLD.

22:18.170 --> 22:19.204
- OF COURSE.

22:19.271 --> 22:20.839
- YAY!

22:20.906 --> 22:22.874
- THIS PLACE
IS SO GREAT.

22:22.941 --> 22:26.044
OOH! I EVEN HAVE
A BEAR SKIN RUG.

22:26.111 --> 22:27.946
[bear roars]

22:28.013 --> 22:30.782
STAY AWAY
FROM MY BALL GOWNS!

22:30.849 --> 22:32.150
-<i> BUENOS DIAS.</i>

22:32.217 --> 22:34.186
I GOT THE PASSPORTS.

22:34.252 --> 22:35.854
- MAGIC WEENIE!
